               <textBox id="action">
                  <label>Action taken</label>
                  <p>A meeting was help this afternoon at 2 p.m. in the office of Dean Vincent Inc. It closed the sale of the subject hotel. There were present Rogers..representing Metropolitan Life Insurance owner's of the property;<person project-ref="JAIFRP-00133">Andy Radakovich</person>attorney for the purchaser;<person project-ref="JAIFRP-00132">H.W. Johnson</person>, real estate broker; Morris Goldstein Jr. representing he father, holder of the mortgage agasint the hotel furnishings</p>
                  <p>under power of attorney;<person project-ref="JAIFRP-00120">Mr. T. E. Linden Sr.</person>. representing his son, owner of the consideration paid for the property was $1700.00 out of which was taken $1303.14 to satisfy the mortgage and all back interest owed by <person project-ref="JAIFRP-00122">Kimi Anazawa</person> to <person project-ref="JAIFRP-00129">C. Uyesugi</person>. As the seller had agreed to a selling price of $1500</p>
                  <p><person project-ref="JAIFRP-00132">H.W. Johnson</person> received $100 commision in addition to the earnest money deposit of $100 which he had been holding since about June 4th. A slight verbal controversay took place between <person project-ref="JAIFRP-00120">T.E. Linden Sr.</person> and <person project-ref="JAIFRP-00132">Mr H.W. Johnson</person> over the balance of the additional $100 which <person project-ref="JAIFRP-00120">Mr. Linden</person> finally paid,</p>
                  <p>admitting that his memory was a little faulty as to the net selling rules. He was reminded of the fact that his son had agreed to sell the hotel for $1500 net early in May. The sale and occupancy by the new owner as of July 1st, all rentals, utilities, and bills being adjusted as of that date.</p>
